# Jewelry Casting Pipeline Rules

Read SOPs in `docs/` before modifying any mesh.

## Units and import

- Set Blender scene to **Metric**, display **mm**, unit scale **1.0**
- On import: **Apply All Transforms** before measuring
- Verify bounding box ~20–24 mm × 20–24 mm × 6–10 mm for rings (scale sanity)

## Ring sizing

- Target inner diameter from `docs/ring-size-chart.md` (US 8 = 18.14 mm ID)
- **Never uniform-scale head + band together** for finger sizing
- Separate band from head (bisect at shank/head junction), scale band only, rejoin and clean seam
- Band/head separation is **supervised** — assist user, do not run unsupervised
- Log before/after inner diameter in mm

## Shrinkage

- **Ask** metal alloy and castable resin brand before applying scale
- Use `docs/shrinkage-table.md` — never guess shrinkage factor
- Confirm whether casting house applies their own compensation (avoid double-scaling)

## Blender add-ons (casting CAD)

Required extensions — see `docs/setup-macos.md` for install:

- **3D Print Toolbox** — wall thickness, manifold, overhang checks
- **MeasureIt** — dimension verification
- **LoopTools**, **Bool Tool**, **Extra Mesh Objects** — modeling cleanup
- **JewelCraft** — gems, bezels, prongs (solitaire settings)
- **CAD Sketcher** — parametric constrained sketches (experimental; keep backups)

## Wall thickness and hollow

- Minimum wall: **0.8 mm** sterling (prefer **1.0 mm** for safer casting)
- Use 3D Print Toolbox to flag thin areas
- If hollowed: require **≥1 mm drain hole** oriented for flask drainage

## Sprue

- **Manual only** — see `docs/sprue-placement-sop.md`
- Do **not** auto-generate sprues via MCP

## Checkpointing

Export versioned STL after each major step; **never overwrite**:

`ring_v01_raw-export` → `v02_meshmixer-repaired` → `v03_blender-imported` → `v04_sized` → `v05_hollowed` → `v06_cast-ready`

Stop if manifold gate fails. Revert to previous checkpoint.

## Mesh health gate

Do not proceed in Blender until Meshmixer repair passes (see `docs/mesh-health-gate.md`).

## Gem enclosure (stone lock)

Read `docs/eastwest-signet-workflow.md` before modifying any head or setting.

- Stone must be **mechanically locked** — metal overlaps short ends with bearing below girdle and lip above
- Build seat by boolean-subtracting an offset gem copy; never leave pillars beside the stone
- Keep long sides (±Z) and table open; verify with adversarial ray-tests before export
- Shoulder geometry must not intrude into finger bore (preserve target ID)
- Run gates: lip, bearing, table open, long-side open, manifold 0, wall under pavilion ≥0.8 mm
- Stop and revert checkpoint if any gate fails

## Scope limits (v1)

- **Blender 5.1.2** with [official Blender Lab MCP](https://www.blender.org/lab/mcp-server/) only — not third-party ahujasid addon
- MCP executes LLM Python in Blender unsandboxed — jewelry scenes only, no sensitive blend files
- Simple bands and signet / semi-bezel settings
- Defer automated sprue to v2; stone-seat adversarial review is required (see workflow doc)
- Decimate to ~50–100K tris before complex booleans if poly count >500K
- Save `.blend` to `fixtures/` after major head iterations
